The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Migrants
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                      Migrants
                            
	Jammu, April 2 (PTI): The Centre has increased cash assistance for Kashmiri migrants from Rs 4,000 to Rs 5,000, the Jammu and Kashmir government said today.        
	The minister for revenue, relief and rehabilitation, Raman Bhalla, said the Centre has approved Rs 1,618.40 crore for rehabilitation of displaced families in the Valley.        
	The government has created 3,000 posts for educated unemployed Kashmiri migrant youths, Bhalla said, adding that 3,000 more posts would be created.        
	The government has also constructed a township of 4,218 flats at Jagti, near Jammu, for the Kashmiri migrants.                                                                                                                                                          
